.TH "mempool_exit" 9 "mempool_exit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mempool_exit \- exit a mempool initialized with mempool_init()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mempool_exit
.BI "(mempool_t *pool "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pointer to the memory pool which was initialized with
\fBmempool_init\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Free all reserved elements in \fIpool\fP and \fIpool\fP itself.  This function
only sleeps if the \fBfree_fn\fP function sleeps.

May be called on a zeroed but uninitialized mempool (i.e. allocated with
\fBkzalloc\fP).
